FBIS4-58147 "drnes084_s_94003" FBIS-NES-94-084 Daily Report 1 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA Iran Irish Prime Minister Denies IRA-Iran Links Irish Prime Minister Denies IRA-Iran Links LD0105171194 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 1 May 94 LD0105171194 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Sinn Fein, the political wing of the IRA, has denied any links with the Islamic Republic of Iran. A Sinn Fein spokesman said that the British allegations are some vague propaganda without any basis and foundations. Moreover, Irish Prime Minister Albert Reynolds said that he was unaware of any links between the IRA and Iran. He said that so far he has not seen any firm evidences and reasons to prove the British claim. The London daily TIMES wrote that the British accusation against Iran is a biased political move, which have been carried out with America's coordination.
